# project-hints.yaml — optional, per-project topic hints for the Librarian's classify step.
#
# Copy this file to `.memoria/project-hints.yaml` and edit it for your own projects.
# Absent file = project membership is fully manual (no agent proposal). See ADR-15.
#
# How it's used: at classify time the ingest engine scores each project's `primary_topics`
# against the paper's enrichment topic signals (the OpenAlex topic names and subfields,
# kebab-case normalized; `mhealth` matches `mhealth-apps`) by simple overlap, and proposes
# every project with at least one match — ranked by overlap — in the note's
# `_proposed_classification` block. The human confirms or corrects the `projects` value at
# triage, exactly like every other proposed field. The decision is audited in
# system/logs/classify.jsonl.
#
# A hint is a HINT, not a controlled vocabulary — edit `primary_topics` freely. Do NOT add
# `expected_study_designs` / `expected_methods` matrices here (ADR-15 rejected them as
# drift-prone; study_design and methods are proposed independently).

projects:
  - id: phd-dissertation
    description: >-
      Replace with your project's one-line scope. Example: HCI + digital health — JITAI,
      receptivity, health coaching, equity, LLM mHealth.
    primary_topics: [jitai, receptivity-detection, health-coaching, mhealth, sensemaking, health-equity]

  - id: scoping-review
    description: Replace with the actual scope of this project.
    primary_topics: [jitai, mhealth]
